Abi Webster (Sally Carman) is in for a huge surprise as Coronation Street commences its brand new ITV timeslot. What started off with a joyride, quickly unfolds into a ‘bundle of joy’, as she’s dumped at the side of the road in agonising labour. Life has never been smooth-sailing for Abi, but things were finally starting to look up after the tragic murder of her eldest son Seb. Marrying Kevin and trying to legally adopt Jack, it looked like Abi was getting her life back on track. “‘his is the brilliant thing about Abi; for all the life knocks, she’s such a fighter and because she’s got such a big heart, if there’s a grain of hope or crack of light, she will dive for it,’ says Sally Carman. Unfortunately, Abi just can’t seem to catch a break. Last week we saw the beginning of another epic downward spiral for everyone’s favourite mechanic, as her one-night stand was revealed and her family with Kevin and Jack was left in ruins. {"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"VideoObject","name":"Metro.co.uk","duration":"T41S","thumbnailUrl":"https://i.dailymail.co.uk/1s/2022/03/04/17/54958337-0-image-a-9_1646413647596.jpg","uploadDate":"2022-03-04T17:04:59+0000","description":"As Dean soothes Abi's back pain with a massage, they are shocked when Kevin enters - with his worst fears realised as he sees their intimacy and the empty vodka bottles.","contentUrl":"https://videos.metro.co.uk/video/met/2022/03/04/6086037053834771750/480x270_MP4_6086037053834771750.mp4","height":270,"width":480}  To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web
